Reasoning: The paper discusses the performance of message-passing decoding algorithms for LDPC codes in the high-rate regime, which is a topic closely related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also extends the analysis to compressed sensing (CS) of strictly-sparse signals, which falls under the category of cs.CC (computational complexity) and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). The use of density evolution and stopping-set based approaches also suggests a connection to statistical inference (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.MM).
